-- French Highway Tolls to Rise 2.5% in February, Le Figaro Says
-- B y   R u d y   R u i t e n b e r g
-- 2011-12-15T06:43:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-15/french-highway-tolls-to-rise-2-5-in-february-le-figaro-says.html
French highway tolls will rise an
average 2.5 percent as of Feb. 1, more than inflation, Le Figaro
reported, citing government announcements.  Societe des Autoroutes Paris-Normandie will raise tariffs
by 3.03 percent, the most among the highway operators, the
newspaper said.  Societe des Autoroutes Paris-Rhin-Rhone (ARR)  will
charge 2.58 percent more and Autoroutes du Sud de la France SA
will raise prices by 2.42 percent, according to  Le Figaro .  Vinci SA (DG) ’s Autoroutes Esterel Cote d’Azur Provence Alpes
will lift tariffs by 1.71 percent, the smallest increase, the
daily said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rudy Ruitenberg in Paris at 
 rruitenberg@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net . 